<p><strong>Colors:</strong> 
If the last reported cases are &lt; 25% of the maximum, the data is shown in green. Else, if the last cases are &gt; 75% of the maximum, the data is shown in red. Else, grey.</p>
<p><strong>Axes:</strong> 
The data is shown on a <strong>normalized y-axis</strong>. This means that the actual numbers between countries can be very different and should not be compared. On the x-axis, the data is shown from the day of the 100th positive case until today.</p>
<p><strong>Preprocessing:</strong>
The number of new cases per day is averaged using a 10-day rolling window. Countries are included if they have at least 1000 cases and at least 100 deaths. Countries are sorted by total number of cases.</p>
<p><strong>Data:</strong> The data is pulled from the COVID-19 <a href="https://github.com/CSSEGISandData/COVID-19/tree/master/csse_covid_19_data/csse_covid_19_time_series">Data Repository</a> by Johns Hopkins CSSE</p>
